nodes.title: Learn the basics of programming
nodes.desc: Understand the fundamental concepts of programming, including data types, variables, control structures, functions, and object-oriented programming. [Codecademy](https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-to-code)

nodes.title: Choose a programming language
nodes.desc: Select a language to focus on, such as Python, JavaScript, or Java, and learn its syntax, semantics, and ecosystem. [Python.org](https://www.python.org/)

nodes.title: Learn cybersecurity
nodes.desc: Understand the basics of cybersecurity, including security threats, vulnerabilities, and risk management, and learn how to secure applications and data. [OWASP](https://owasp.org/)

nodes.title: Learn agile development
nodes.desc: Study agile development methodologies like Scrum or Kanban, and learn how to work in an agile team. [Scrum.org](https://www.scrum.org/)

nodes.title: Learn design patterns
nodes.desc: Study design patterns like Singleton, Factory, or Observer, and learn how to apply them to real-world problems. [Design Patterns](https://www.designpatterns.com/)

nodes.title: Learn microservices architecture
nodes.desc: Understand the basics of microservices architecture, including service discovery, communication, and deployment, and learn how to design and implement microservices. [Microservices.io](https://microservices.io/)

nodes.title: Learn containerization
nodes.desc: Study containerization using Docker, and learn how to containerize applications and deploy them to the cloud. [Docker](https://www.docker.com/)

nodes.title: Learn serverless computing
nodes.desc: Understand the basics of serverless computing, including AWS Lambda or Azure Functions, and learn how to build and deploy serverless applications. [AWS Lambda](https://aws.amazon.com/lambda/)

nodes.title: Learn machine learning
nodes.desc: Study machine learning concepts, including supervised and unsupervised learning, neural networks, and deep learning, and learn how to apply them to real-world problems. [Machine Learning Crash Course](https://developers.google.com/machine-learning/crash-course)

nodes.title: Learn data science
nodes.desc: Understand the basics of data science, including data wrangling, visualization, and modeling, and learn how to apply them to real-world problems. [Data Science Handbook](https://jakevdp.github.io/PythonDataScienceHandbook/)

nodes.title: Learn UX design
nodes.desc: Study UX design principles, including user research, wireframing, and usability testing, and learn how to design user-centered applications. [UX Design](https://www.usability.gov/)

nodes.title: Learn project management
nodes.desc: Understand the basics of project management, including project planning, scheduling, and risk management, and learn how to manage projects effectively. [Project Management Institute](https://www.pmi.org/)

nodes.title: Set up a development environment
nodes.desc: Install a code editor or IDE, such as Visual Studio Code, IntelliJ, or Sublime Text, and familiarize yourself with its features. [Visual Studio Code](https://code.visualstudio.com/)

nodes.title: Learn data structures and algorithms
nodes.desc: Study arrays, linked lists, stacks, queues, trees, and graphs, as well as algorithms like sorting, searching, and graph traversal. [GeeksforGeeks](https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/)

nodes.title: Learn web development
nodes.desc: Understand the basics of web development, including HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, and learn frameworks like React, Angular, or Vue.js. [FreeCodeCamp](https://www.freecodecamp.org/)

nodes.title: Learn database management
nodes.desc: Study database concepts, including data modeling, normalization, and querying, and learn database management systems like MySQL or MongoDB. [W3Schools](https://www.w3schools.com/sql/)

nodes.title: Learn version control
nodes.desc: Understand the basics of version control, including Git, and learn how to use GitHub or other version control systems. [GitHub](https://github.com/)

nodes.title: Learn testing and debugging
nodes.desc: Study testing frameworks like Jest or Pytest, and learn how to write unit tests, integration tests, and debug code. [Jest](https://jestjs.io/)

nodes.title: Learn DevOps
nodes.desc: Understand the basics of DevOps, including continuous integration, continuous deployment, and continuous monitoring, and learn tools like Jenkins or Docker. [Jenkins](https://jenkins.io/)

nodes.title: Learn cloud computing
nodes.desc: Study cloud computing platforms like AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud, and learn how to deploy and manage applications in the cloud. [AWS](https://aws.amazon.com/)
